Conor Oberst's new album Upside Down Mountain is due out in May. In an interview with Rolling Stone earlier this year, Oberst talked about paring down certain elements for the record's new direction. "I don't relate to a lot of my earlier songs," he said. "They were extremely verbose. That might be cathartic when you're doing it, but it doesn't necessarily hold up."
